715724f-a.text:
West 165th Street, west from Amsterdam Avenue, showing at the right the area to be cleared for steet widening. This will leave a triangular plasa facing the R. C. Church of St. Rose of Lima (left). Beyond the solitary tenement that is to be demolished, avupears a glimpse of the Wm. Fox Audubon Theatre.
April 30, 1924
Standard Photographic Service
Gift of Borough Preeident of Manhattan

715725f-a.text:
West 165th Street, east from Audubon to Amsterdam Avenue, showing the 4 story tenement (with undertaking sign) that is to be removed in the regulating and grading contract. To the right appears the R. C. Church of St. Rose of Lima. In the foreground are the St. Nicholas Avenue cartracks.
April 30, 1924
Standard Photographic Service
Gift of Borough President of Manhattan
